# Line-ending policy: the repo stores LF (2,038 of 2,060 tracked text files
# already do). This overrides any developer's local core.autocrlf so editor
# or OS differences can't silently reintroduce CRLF churn into diffs.
#
# Known exception: ~19 files were historically committed with CRLF (e.g.
# package.json, src/app/layout.js, src/context/DashboardContext.js). They
# stay untouched until a deliberate one-time normalization commit
# (`git add --renormalize .`) — until then they may show a whole-file
# line-ending diff the first time they're edited. That's expected, not data
# loss.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binaries — never normalize.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.webp binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
*.mp4 binary
*.mov binary
*.zip binary
